{{!
    @template core/tabs

    Moodle tabs template.

    The purpose of this template is to render a list of tabs
    with content.

    Classes required for JS:
    *

    Data attributes required for JS:
    * role="tablist" Required on the element that contains the tabs.
    * role="tab" Required to flag an element as a tab. Must be within a tab list.
    * data-target Required on tab element. Must match id of tab panel.
    * data-selected-class Optional to specify which class gets applied to a tab and
    *   it's panel when it is selected. This will default to 'active', if not provided.
    * role="tabpanel" Required on each panel element.
    * id Required on each panel element and must match a data-target on a tab.

    Context variables required for this template:
    * tabs A list of objects to represent. See below:
    ** active (optional) bool Should this tab be active by default.
    ** id Identifier to uniquely identify this tab within the list.
    ** name Display name for the tab
    ** content Content to display in the tab panel for this tab.

    Example context (json):
    {
        "tabs": [
            {"selected":true,"id":"tab1","name":"Tab 1","content":"This is tab 1 content <a href=\"#\">test</a>"},
            {"id":"tab2","name":"Tab 2","content":"This is tab 2 content <a href=\"#\">test</a>"},
            {"id":"tab3","name":"Tab 3","content":"This is tab 3 content <a href=\"#\">test</a>"}
        ]
    }
}}
<div id="{{ uniqid }}-tab-container" class="tabtree">
    {{$ tabheader }}
        {{> core/tab_header }}
    {{/ tabheader }}
    {{$ tabbody }}
        {{> core/tab_content }}
    {{/ tabbody }}
</div>
{{#js}}
    require(['jquery','core/tabs'], function($, tabs) {

        var container = $("#{{ uniqid }}-tab-container");
        tabs.create(container);
    });
{{/js}}
